{
  "stem": "24409.12",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had an-- I had a friend-- he had a friend, Richard.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I called him Rick-- I don't know now his second name; doesn't come to my mind now-- who was very interested in Holocaust and was a real researcher, who helped me very much by getting me data from the Library of Congress.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I always had people who were more as friends of mine and who went for me to the various libraries and looked up what I wanted to know.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was, for-- for this year, for the [INAUDIBLE], I was in England for about three months and studied there very carefully in the Public Records Office, which is their national archive.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What they had there is I have many documentage people-- [? other ?] [? people ?] [? that ?] [? was ?] [? interested ?] [? in it ?] and which I discovered is very important.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I have two sons.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The older one is a lawyer and with the Library of Congress.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He's one of the better-informed men about notorious men's [? drugs ?] now, too.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Rafael Perl.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He's on many panels, and he wrote some books-- I think two books.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, he wrote another book, too, on [INAUDIBLE] the Falkland Islands.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's a legal situation of the Falkland Islands, when the war-- the dispute was between Great Britain and Argentina.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and the younger son is a veterinarian, who has a-- he doesn't want to work for anybody and want to be-- doesn't want to be tied to any-- [? tied down. ?] So he-- very original.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He established himself as a house-call veterinarian.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And [? there's ?] a tremendous demand for it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He makes house calls.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he-- he-- many people prefer not to go to the veterinarian's office.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
